<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1724,2039]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">Description.</emphasis>
Body 
<quantity box="[379,518,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.7 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[641,731,1724,1751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
wide (N=3), elliptical, highly convex in lateral view, pilose (
<figureCitation box="[159,262,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[275,320,1760,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">5, 6</figureCitation>
). Color dark brown with whitish and black hair on elytra. Head hypognathous, convex, with frons and vertex forming about 135º angle in lateral view. Vertex densely covered with large setiferous pores (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1422,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Supraorbital pore indistinguishable. Antennal calli not separated from rest of head surface, quadrate, punctured as vertex. Midfrontal, suprafrontal, supracallual, suprantennal and supraorbital sulci present. Orbit as narrow as diameter of antennal socket. Interantennal space wide, as wide as the length of first antennomere. Antennal socket small, rounded. Eye small, rounded, slightly projected. Frontal and anterofrontal ridges connected, wide, raised, with anterofrontal ridge extending to clypeal margin, punctured, with setae directed inward (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1259,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeal suture present. Clypeus narrow with six setae, four long and two short. Labrum with anterior angles rounded and six setiferous pores bearing long seta. Gena slightly punctured, pilose. First and second maxillary palpomere slightly wider and longer than third; third palpomere conical, with acute apex. Labial palpomeres similar in size, third with acute apex. Antenna with 11 antennomeres; antennomeres VI to X moniliform, densely pilose (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1285,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" startId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" targetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1958,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,317,1958,1982]" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">FIGURES 1–4.</emphasis>
