<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">
Pronotum rectangular, densely punctate, wider than long, margined laterally; anterior margin straight; posterior margin slightly concave; anterior and posterior angles well-defined, prominent, with a setiferous pore bearing a long seta. Scutellum triangular, small, smooth and pilose (
<figureCitation box="[739,809,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[822,838,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">5</figureCitation>
). Elytra elliptical, with apex narrower. Elytral surface shiny, punctured, pilose with three small, rounded patches of white setae. Punctures forming nine striae between short scutellar and marginal striae; fourth and fifth rows of punctures merge and terminate in posterior half. Interstriae convex (
<figureCitation box="[314,386,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[398,414,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">7</figureCitation>
). Basal calli not developed. Humeral calli absent. Epipleura wide, vertical, visible in lateral view, nearly reaching elytral apex. Membranous wings absent. Prosternum narrow, with prosternal process as wide as anterior arms of prosternum; prosternal process extended and widened posteriorly beyond coxa, posteriorly about twice as wide as middle. Procoxa elongate. Procoxal cavities closed posteriorly. Mesoventrite narrow, margined; mesoventral process slightly wider than prosternal process. Metaventrite wide, margined; anterior margin slightly punctured; posterior margin concave medially.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="103" startId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" targetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1956,2017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,327,1956,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">FIGURES 9–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov" authorityName="Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov" authorityYear="2021" box="[333,932,1957,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Brasilplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahianus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[333,556,1957,1981]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="103">Brasilplatus bahianus</emphasis>
Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[941,1066,1957,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="103" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
Pro- and mesofemora slightly dilated medially; pro- and mesotibiae subcylindrical, dorsal margins straight, parallel (in dorsal view), slightly narrower at apex (in lateral view), pubescence sparsely distributed; pro- and mesotibial apex with a crown of denticles. First pro- and mesotarsomeres 1.5 times longer than second; second short; third bilobed; fourth tarsomere narrow, as long as second and third together; claws appendiculate. Metafemur greatly enlarged, about 1.5 times longer than wide, longer than metatibia, sparsely pilose, outer side convex, inner side flat (
<figureCitation box="[259,362,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[377,393,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">6</figureCitation>
). Metatibia as long as half-length of metafemur, nearly straight, with a preapical projection in lateral view, slightly curved in dorsal view; outer dorsal ridge with preapical projection. Metatibial spur short. Metatarsomeres inserted preapically. First metatarsomere 1.5 times longer than second; second and third short; third not bilobed; fourth globose; metatarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
Abdomen with five visible ventrites. Ventrite V distinctly sexually dimorphic: males with concavity medially on posterior margin and longitudinal medial line; females with last ventrite conical at apex. Pygidium apically exposed. Median lobe simple, tubular, slightly concave in lateral view, apex subtriangular (Figs 9,10). Female sternite eight triangular, medially slightly concave, with setae on apex. Tignum simple, spoon like (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1266,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Vaginal palpi parallel, each with sides slightly divergent, apical half of palpi externally rounded and obliquely truncate to rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[219,303,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca with receptacle, pump and canal distinct (
