<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="104" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,691,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is formed from two words, 
<emphasis box="[867,935,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<collectingCountry box="[867,935,691,717]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Brasil</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, referring to the flea beetle’s native country and 
<emphasis box="[199,267,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">platus</emphasis>
refering to its placement in 
<taxonomicName box="[583,726,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Monoplatina">Monoplatina</taxonomicName>
(from 
<taxonomicName box="[804,938,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Monoplatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,938,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Monoplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1177,762,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104" type="type_taxon">
